- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of a distributed cloud system for high throughput computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper specifically focuses on the use of the system for high energy physics data analysis. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the system involves accessing a central database and streaming data. 
- cs.Distributed Systems is relevant as the paper discusses the design of a distributed cloud system. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of a central database for calibration data.
